fn.p:
Additional distribution: other foreign regions in which a species is now established. Zone: 
                                T, temperate zone of Europe; 
                                M, Mediterranean zone; 
                                B, boreal zone; 
                                gh, greenhouse populations. 
                                Feeds: 
                                Xm, xylomycetophagous (ambrosia beetle); 
                                Phl, phloeophagous, breeding in bark; 
                                Spm, spermatophagous, breeding in seeds (terminology from 
                                Wood 1982). *
                                
                                    Xyleborus pfeilii is highly polyphagous in conifers and broadleaf trees in Japan (
                                Mizuno and Kajimura 2002) though the few host records in Europe are from 
                                
                                    Alnus and 
                                
                                    Betula (e.g. 
                                Balachowsky 1949).
